•	The route with the highest probability is selected as the optimal route 
•	Higher penalty values enforce single-route selection 
•	Lower penalty values allow multi-route combinations 
•	The results demonstrate that:
•	The algorithm successfully converges to the lowest-cost route 
•	Quantum superposition enables exploration of multiple possibilities simultaneously 
•	The model effectively balances cost and operational constraints 
